Niue|associated states]] of [[Cook Islands]] and [[Niue]] and the dependent territory [[Tokelau]].<ref name=\"WHO Dashboard\">{{cite web|url=https://covid19.who.int/|title=WHO COVID-19 Dashboard|date=17 April 2020|accessdate=17 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n{{as of|2020|4|20}}, there are 16 significant [[Disease cluster|clusters]] of 10 or more confirmed and probable COVID-19 cases:<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.health.govt.nz/our-work/diseases-and-conditions/covid-19-novel-coronavirus/covid-19-current-situation/covid-19-current-cases/covid-19-clusters|title=COVID-19 \u2013 Clusters|website=Ministry of Health NZ|language=en|access-date=2020-03-31}}</ref>\n[[File:Bluff - 27072304573.jpg|thumb|Oyster Cove, the venue of the Bluff wedding at [[Stirling Point]]]]\n\n*Wedding, [[Bluff, New Zealand|Bluff]] \u2013 96\n*[[Marist College, Auckland|Marist College]], [[Auckland]] \u2013 93\n*Redoubt Bar, [[Matamata]] \u2013 76\n*Rosewood rest home, [[Christchurch]] \u2013 43\n*World [[Hereford cattle|Hereford]] Conference, [[Queenstown, New Zealand|Queenstown]] \u2013 39\n*Private function, Auckland \u2013 38\n*Community group, Auckland \u2013 30\n*CHT St Margarets rest home, Auckland \u2013 25\n*''[[Ruby Princess]]'' cruise ship, [[Hawke's Bay Region|Hawke's Bay]] \u2013 22\n*George Manning Lifecare rest home, Christchurch \u2013 20\n*Group travel to the United States, [[Wellington]] \u2013 16\n*Group travel to the United States, Auckland \u2013 16\n*Atawhai Assisi rest home, [[Hamilton, New Zealand|Hamilton]] \u2013 14\n*Rest home, Auckland \u2013 14\n*Wedding, Wellington \u2013 13\n*Workplace, Christchurch \u2013 10\n\n===Progression of COVID-19===\nProgression of COVID-19 cases in New Zealand:<ref name=\"The New Zealand Ministry of Health\">{{cite web |title=The New Zealand Ministry of Health |url=https://www.health.govt.nz/news-media/media-releases|website=Health.govt.nz}}</ref>\n{{Graph:Chart\n | width=900\n | height=450\n | xAxisTitle=Date\n | yAxisTitle=Count\n | xType=string\