nd on the Shetland Islands for [[Up Helly Aa]], the biggest fire festival in Europe.\n |LineColor       = e3cd81\n}}\n|}\n\n===Series 2 (2014)===\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"width:100%; margin:auto; background:#fff;\"\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"background:#4fa8ff; color:#000; text-align:center;\"|Overall<br />No.\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"background:#4fa8ff; color:#000; text-align:center;\"|Episode<br />No.\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"background:#4fa8ff; color:#000; text-align:center;\"|Title\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"background:#4fa8ff; color:#000; text-align:center;\"|Directed by\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"background:#4fa8ff; color:#000; text-align:center;\"|Written by\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"background:#4fa8ff; color:#000; text-align:center;\"|Original air date\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"background:#4fa8ff; color:#000; text-align:center;\"|UK viewers<br/>(million)<ref name=ratings>{{cite web|url=http://www.barb.co.uk/viewingsummary/weekreports.cfm?report=weeklyterrestrial&requesttimeout=500 |publisher=[[Broadcasters' Audience Research Board|BARB]] |title=Weekly Viewing Summary (see relevant week) |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20080713000000/http://www.barb.co.uk/viewingsummary/weekreports.cfm?report=weeklyterrestrial&RequestTimeout=500 |archivedate=13 July 2008 }}</ref>\n{{Episode list/sublist|Shetland (TV series)\n |EpisodeNumber   = 3\n |EpisodeNumber2  = 1\n |Title           = Raven Black \u2013 Part 1\n |DirectedBy      = [[John McKay (director)|John McKay]]\n |WrittenBy       = [[Gaby Chiappe]]\n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|df=yes|2014|03|11}}\n |Aux4            = 6.37\n |ShortSummary    = DI Jimmy Perez and his team investigate the murder of a teenage girl whose body was found on a secluded beach, and time and again the same name crops up \u2013 that of local recluse Magnus Bain, whose home overlooks the crime scene and who had forged an unlikely friendship with the victim. But then the [[procurator fiscal]] draws attention to the unsolved disappearance of a girl named Catriona 19 years previously \u2013 a case that shares several similarities with this one.\n |LineColor       = 4fa8ff\n}}\n{{Episode list/sublist|Shetland (TV series)\n |EpisodeNumber   = 4\n |EpisodeNumber2  = 2\n |Title           = Raven Black \u2013 Part 2\n |DirectedBy      = John McKay\n |WrittenBy       = [[Gaby Chiappe]]\n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|df=yes|2014|03|18}}\n |Aux4            = 6.16\n |ShortSummary    = The discovery of seven-year-old Catriona's body after almost two decades prompts Jimmy Perez to take Magnus in for further questioning. But at the station, the recluse's distress leads to his attacking the inspector, and Magnus is sent for a psychological evaluation. Ploughing on, Perez re-examines the evidence, but it is only when Catriona's brother reveals she had a secret hiding place at their old home \u2013 the same house where Catherine also lived \u2013 that he finally sees a glimmer of hope.\n |LineColor       = 4fa8ff\n}}\n{{Episode list/sublist|Shetland (TV series)\n |EpisodeNumber   = 5\n |EpisodeNumber2  = 3\n |Title           = Dead Water \u2013 Part 1\n |DirectedBy      = David Moore\n |WrittenBy       = David Kane\n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|df=yes|2014|03|25}}\n |Aux4            = 5.56\n |ShortSummary    = A journalist dies in a suspicious car accident, and when it turns out he was an old friend of Perez's, a forensic scientist is called in to ensure an objective view of the case. As the team awaits her results, they look into the reasons for the victim's return to the island and find he was chasing a lead about plans for a controversial new gas pipeline.\n |LineColor       = 4fa8ff\n}}\n{{Episode list/sublist|Shetland (TV series)\n |EpisodeNumber   = 6\n |EpisodeNumber2  = 4\n |Title           = Dead Water \u2013 Part 2\n |DirectedBy      = David Moore\n |WrittenBy       = David Kane\n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|df=yes|2014|04|01}}\n |Aux4            = 5.53\n |ShortSummary    = The discovery of John Henderson's body leads DI Perez to wonder if this second killing is linked to the death of his journalist friend Jerry, a theory given greater weight by forensic investigator Willow Reeves' finds. But then the case takes another surprising turn with the arrival of Jerry's fiancee, carrying a memory stick he gave to her for safekeeping several weeks earlier.\n |LineColor       = 4fa8ff\n}}\n{{Episode list/sublist|Shetland (TV series)\n |EpisodeNumber   = 7\n |EpisodeNumber2  = 5\n |Title           = Blue Lightning \u2013 Part 1\n |DirectedBy      = Stewart Svaasand\n |WrittenBy       = Richard Davidson\n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|df=yes|2014|04|08}}\n |Aux4            = 5.29\n |ShortSummary    = A scientist is found dead in the bird observatory on [[Fair Isle]], Perez's childhood home, so Perez and Tosh  make their way across to the island, where they are greeted by Perez's father \u2013 just before flights are grounded by incoming storms. Working alone and without a forensic team, the detectives talk to the victim's friends, family, and colleagues \u2013 and as tensions run high, the storm forces Perez and the suspects to remain together under a single roof.\n |LineColor       = 4fa8ff\n}}\n{{Episode list/sublist|Shetland (TV series)\n |EpisodeNumber   = 8\n |EpisodeNumber2  = 6\n |Title           = Blue Lightning \u2013 Part 2\n |DirectedBy      = Stewart Svaasand\n |WrittenBy       = Richard Davidson\n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|df=yes|2014|04|15}}\n |Aux4            = 5.33\n |ShortSummary    = Time is running out for Perez and Tosh as their prime suspect lies critically ill in hospital, but it's unclear whether the fire that put him there was a drunken accident or if he was the second victim of Anna's real killer. The DI turns his attention to Finlay Caulfield regarding the photos of Anna on his camera, and while it becomes clear he was obsessed with her, it may not be enough to charge the stalker with her murder. There are still so many unanswered questions \u2013 until Sandy spots something on the CCTV footage that takes the investigation in a new direction.\n |LineColor       = 4fa8ff\n}}\n|}\n\n===Series 3 (2016)===\nThe broadcast of Episode 6 was delayed due to coverage of an [[FA Cup]] replay being broadcast.  In contrast to Season 2 (3, 2-part episodes), Season 3 is one 6-part story.\n\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"width:100%; margin:auto; background:#fff;\"\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"background:#6df9dd; color:#000; text-align:center;\"|Overall<br />No.\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"background:#6df9dd; color:#000; text-align:center;\"|Episode<br />No.\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"background:#6df9dd; color:#000; text-align:center;\"|Title\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"background:#6df9dd; color:#000; text-align:center;\"|Directed by\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"background:#6df9dd; color:#000; text-align:center;\"|Written by\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"background:#6df9dd; color:#000; text-align:center;\"|UK air date\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"background:#6df9dd; color:#000; text-align:center;\"|UK viewers<br/>(million)<ref name=\"ratings\"/>\n{{Episode list/sublist|Shetland (TV series)\n |EpisodeNumber   = 9\n |EpisodeNumber2  = 1\n |Title           = Episode 1\n |DirectedBy      = [[Thaddeus O'Sullivan]]\n |WrittenBy       = [[Gaby Chiappe]]\n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|df=yes|2016|01|15}}\n |Aux4            = 6.82\n |ShortSummary    = When a young man disappears on a ferry crossing and a small boy ends up in intensive care after overdosing on Ecstasy, Perez and the team become convinced the two events are connected.\n |LineColor       = 6df9dd\n}}\n{{Episode list/sublist|Shetland (TV series)\n |EpisodeNumber   = 10\n |EpisodeNumber2  = 2\n |Title           = Episode 2\n |DirectedBy      = Thaddeus O'Sullivan\n |WrittenBy       = Robert Murphy\n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|df=yes|2016|01|22}}\n |Aux4            = 6.02\n |ShortSummary    = Perez grows convinced that Michael Maguire is implicated in the grisly death of a young man, discovered in a shipping container.\n |LineColor       = 6df9dd\n}}\n{{Episode list/sublist|Shetland (TV series)\n |EpisodeNumber   = 11\n |EpisodeNumber2  = 3\n |Title           = Episode 3\n |DirectedBy      = Thaddeus O'Sullivan\n |WrittenBy       = Robert Murphy\n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|df=yes|2016|02|05}}\n |Aux4            = 6.21\n |ShortSummary    = Perez and Tosh's investigation leads them to Glasgow, where they hope to uncover the truth behind Maguire's brutal death and his connection to Robbie Morton. Old ghosts return to haunt Perez, with his enemies trying to prevent him from getting to the truth.\n |LineColor       = 6df9dd\n}}\n{{Episode list/sublist|Shetland (TV series)\n |EpisodeNumber   = 12\n |EpisodeNumber2  = 4\n |Title           = Episode 4\n |DirectedBy      = Jan Matthys\n |WrittenBy       = [[Gaby Chiappe]] & Alexander Perrin\n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|df=yes|2016|02|12}}\n |Aux4            = 6.26\n |ShortSummary    = Perez and the team are determined to track down the person who aided Michael Thompson's killer, but as the case gathers pace, the officers involved find they are all under threat. Sandy comes across the killer by chance in a ruined building, and is knocked out. Tosh, returning from Glasgow, is abducted at the airport.\n |LineColor       = 6df9dd\n}}\n{{Episode list/sublist|Shetland (TV series)\n |EpisodeNumber   = 13\n |EpisodeNumber2  = 5\n |Title           = Episode 5\n |DirectedBy      = Jan Matthys\n |WrittenBy       = [[Gaby Chiappe]]\n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|df=yes|2016|02|19}}\n |Aux4            = 6.55\n |ShortSummary    = Tosh returns apparently unharmed, but the truth later comes out. Perez continues to investigate the double murder case, but finds bureaucracy getting in the way, until he tracks down a rape victim and discovers that her attacker was the son of Phyllis Brennan.\n |LineColor       = 6df9dd\n}}\n{{Episode list/sublist|Shetland (TV series)\n |EpisodeNumber   = 14\n |EpisodeNumber2  = 6\n |Title           = Episode 6\n |DirectedBy      = Jan Matthys\n |WrittenBy       = David Kane\n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|df=yes|2016|03|04}}\n |Aux4            = 6.14\n |ShortSummary    = Perez and the team discover that the person responsible for the deaths of Robbie Morton and Michael Thompson is closer to home than they had thought.\n |LineColor       = 6df9dd\n}}\n|}\n\n===Series 4 (2018)===\nThe broadcast of Episode 3 was delayed by 24 hours due to the broadcast of an [[FA Cup]] replay.\n\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"width:100%; margin:auto; background:#fff;\"\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"background:#24c168; color:#000; text-align:center;\"|Overall<br />No.\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"background:#24c168; color:#000; text-align:center;\"|Episode<br />No.\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"background:#24c168; color:#000; text-align:center;\"|Title\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"background:#24c168; color:#000; text-align:center;\"|Directed by\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"background:#24c168; color:#000; text-align:center;\"|Written by\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"background:#24c168; color:#000; text-align:center;\"|UK air date\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"background:#24c168; color:#000; text-align:center;\"|UK viewers<br/>(million)<ref name=\"ratings\"/>\n{{Episode list/sublist|Shetland (TV series)\n |EpisodeNumber   = 15\n |EpisodeNumber2  = 1\n |Title           = Episode 1\n |DirectedBy      = Lee Haven Jones\n |WrittenBy       = David Kane\n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|df=yes|2018|02|13}}\n |Aux4            = 6.72\n |ShortSummary    = Perez and the team are forced to re-open a 23-year-old cold case when convicted murderer, Thomas Malone, is released from prison. The case concerns teenager Lizzie Kilmuir, who was found strangled to death on a kiln. Upon returning to Shetland, Thomas tries to make amends with Lizzie's twin sister, Kate. Meanwhile, local journalist Sally McColl attends the Shetland Folk Festival with a group of her friends, but doesn't return home later that evening. The next day, she is found strangled to death on a kiln, in what looks like a copycat of Lizzie's murder. Perez is forced to break the news to Drew, Sally's father and a former police officer who led the investigation into Lizzie's murder.\n |LineColor       = 24c168\n}}\n{{Episode list/sublist|Shetland (TV series)\n |EpisodeNumber   = 16\n |EpisodeNumber2  = 2\n |Title           = Episode 2\n |DirectedBy      = Lee Haven Jones\n |WrittenBy       = Louise Ironside\n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|df=yes|2018|02|20}}\n |Aux4            = 6.28\n |ShortSummary    = Perez sets out to find out who attacked Thomas, and circumstances point to Benny Ray. Sandy interviews Jo Halley, who claims she saw Sally arguing with someone in Norwegian at the folk festival. Allan Killick reveals that he had realized that Sally had been lying to him when she was alive. A DNA test on a hair found on Lizzie Kilmuir's scarf reveals it is a relative of Alan. However, when Alan's deceased father is tested, it turns out they are not related. Tosh interviews employees at Forst energy, a Norwegian company that Sally had been investigating, and finds a lead from Robbie's wife, but it runs cold when she is paid off. Perez learns that Thomas's trial was unethical, partly because Benny Ray, who testified against Thomas, was a paid informant. \n |LineColor       = 24c168\n}}\n{{Episode list/sublist|Shetland (TV series)\n |EpisodeNumber   = 17\n |EpisodeNumber2  = 3\n |Title           = Episode 3\n |DirectedBy      = Lee Haven Jones\n |WrittenBy       = Paul Logue\n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|df=yes|2018|02|28}}\n |Aux4            = 6.08\n |ShortSummary    = Tosh heads to Norway to track down the mysterious Andreas Hagan, where she meets detective Lars Bleymann, who takes an instant shine to her. Finding herself drawn into a murky world of far right campaigners, Tosh is alarmed when she returns to her hotel room later that night and finds someone going through her belongings. Perez interviews Donna after receiving the results of the DNA test.\n |LineColor       = 24c168\n}}\n{{Episode list/sublist|Shetland (TV series)\n |EpisodeNumber   = 18\n |EpisodeNumber2  = 4\n |Title           = Episode 4\n |DirectedBy      = Rebecca Gatward\n |WrittenBy       = David Kane\n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|df=yes|2018|03|06}}\n |Aux4            = 5.31\n |ShortSummary    = Perez and Tosh find themselves being pursued by the secret service as their investigation in Norway continues, but when their prime suspect, Mathias Soderland, is found shot in the head whilst bearing a sign reading \"traitor\", they are forced to return to Shetland. Perez questions Duncan about a videotape of a birthday party which Lizzie attended in the days before her death, in which he was present. Sandy receives a distress call from Jo Halley and arrives at her croft to find it has been ransacked.\n |LineColor       = 24c168\n}}\n{{Episode list/sublist|Shetland (TV series)\n |EpisodeNumber   = 19\n |EpisodeNumber2  = 5\n |Title           = Episode 5\n |DirectedBy      = Rebecca Gatward\n |WrittenBy       = David Kane\n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|df=yes|2018|03|13}}<ref>{{cite web|url= http://www.bbc.co.uk/mediacentre/proginfo/2018/11/shetland|title= Shetland episode 5|website= [[BBC]] Media Centre|access-date= 12 March 2018}}</ref>\n |Aux4            = 6.21\n |ShortSummary    = Tosh begins to question if Lars could somehow be involved in Sally's murder after picking up that he knew about roadworks that took place on the island a week before he arrived. A review of the CCTV footage of Sally arriving in Norway reveals that her keychain holds a memory stick which contains video footage of Lars attending an NDA meeting. Under scrutiny, Lars admits having assaulted Jo Halley but denies being involved in the murders, claiming that he was witness to the argument between Sally and another man on the night of her death, but Perez is shocked when Lars identifies Duncan.\n |LineColor       = 24c168\n}}\n{{Episode list/sublist|Shetland (TV series)\n |EpisodeNumber   = 20\n |EpisodeNumber2  = 6\n |Title           = Episode 6\n |DirectedBy      = Rebecca Gatward\n |WrittenBy       = David Kane\n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|df=yes|2018|03|20}}<ref>{{cite web|url= http://www.bbc.co.uk/mediacentre/proginfo/2018/12/shetland|title= Shetland episode 6|website= [[BBC]] Media Centre|access-date= 12 March 2018}}</ref>\n |Aux4            = 6.10\n |ShortSummary    = Jimmy realises that he has no choice but to bring Duncan in for questioning. Duncan denies murdering Lizzie and Sally, but does admit to having an affair with Donna Killick. During a review of images found on Sally's memory stick, Sandy finds a picture taken on the Unst Ferry in June 1993, shortly after Lizzie was murdered, that seemingly identifies the killer. When Duncan's DNA matches the sample found on Lizzie's scarf, Jimmy is forced to break the news to Cassie that Alan is her half-brother. After Donna confesses to the murder, Drew McColl tells Perez that he was trying to protect Donna, and that in doing so he killed his daughter, Sally. Finally cleared of both murders, Thomas suffers a fatal heart attack and dies as a free man.\n |LineColor       = 24c168\n}}\n|}\n\n===Series 5 (2019)===\n\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"width:100%; margin:auto; background:#fff;\"\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"background:#96e041; color:#000; text-align:center;\"|Overall<br />No.\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"background:#96e041; color:#000; text-align:center;\"|Episode<br />No.\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"background:#96e041; color:#000; text-align:center;\"|Title\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"background:#96e041; color:#000; text-align:center;\"|Directed by\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"background:#96e041; color:#000; text-align:center;\"|Written by\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"background:#96e041; color:#000; text-align:center;\"|UK 